<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
The Chicago style does not include newspaper articles in the bibliography. All details are included in the footnote. However, some tutor or lecturers may require you to add an entry in the bibliography. An example is provided below. Chicago does not recommend using page numbers for newspaper articles but a section number or edition could be included. For an article publicly accessible on the internet, include the URL at the end of the citation after the year.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author&#8217;s surname, given name. &#34;Title of Article.&#34; <em>Newspaper Title</em>, Month day, year of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s surname, given name">Orange, David</span>. 
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Article">Something Went Wrong in Plane Crash, Experts Say</span>.&#34; 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Newspaper Title">Herald Tribune</span></em>, 
	<span class="hover" title="Month day, year of publication">December 15, 2056</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
